+## Group History Backfill
+
+Hermes can fetch recent Feishu group messages and prepend them to the current
+agent turn as `channel_context`. This lets the bot answer ordinary group
+follow-ups with recent room context without permanently importing the whole
+group transcript into Hermes conversation history.
+
+The Feishu API used is `GET /open-apis/im/v1/messages` with
+`container_id_type=chat`. Feishu requires the bot to be in the queried group.
+For app/tenant-token access to group history, the app must have a message-read
+scope plus `im:message.group_msg`.
+
+```yaml
+feishu:
+  history_backfill: true
+  history_backfill_limit: 20
+  history_backfill_seconds: 1800
+  history_backfill_max_chars: 6000
+  assistant_identity_throttle_messages: 20
+  assistant_identity_throttle_seconds: 600
+```
+
+| Setting | Default | Description |
+|---------|---------|-------------|
+| `history_backfill` | `false` | Fetch recent group messages for the current turn |
+| `history_backfill_limit` | `20` | Maximum historical messages to include |
+| `history_backfill_seconds` | `1800` | Time window before the trigger message |
+| `history_backfill_max_chars` | `6000` | Maximum formatted context characters |
+| `assistant_identity_throttle_messages` | `20` | Suppress repeated assistant self-introductions if one appears in this many recent group messages |
+| `assistant_identity_throttle_seconds` | `600` | Suppress repeated assistant self-introductions if one appears in this many seconds |
+
+History backfill is skipped for Feishu DMs. Deleted messages, the trigger
+message, and Hermes' own prior bot messages are excluded from the context block.
+Merged forwarded messages (`merge_forward`) are expanded through the message
+detail API when possible; nested images and files are cached as normal inbound
+attachments so vision and document handling can reuse the same paths.
+
 ## Deduplication
 
 Inbound messages are deduplicated using message IDs with a 24-hour TTL. The dedup state is persisted across restarts to `~/.hermes/feishu_seen_message_ids.json`.
